The paper proposes a new method for identifying the spatial spread process of infectious diseases on metapopulation networks. This involves developing an optimization algorithm based on dynamical programming, which comprises three procedures. The paper also introduces an identifiability measure based on entropy theory. Given the focus on developing a new algorithm for identifying the spread process, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of dynamical programming suggests a focus on algorithms and optimization, which could place the paper in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with infectious diseases, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these sub-categories deal with modeling and control of complex systems.
